      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="context-grid">
      <div class="context-text">
        <p class="sl">Los Angeles Short-Term Rental Context</p>
        <h2>LA has one of the highest Airbnb concentrations in the US</h2>
        <p>West Hollywood and Silver Lake are among the densest short-term rental neighborhoods in the country. WeHo's walkability, proximity to the Sunset Strip, and concentration of boutique apartments makes it a perennial top LA Airbnb destination. Silver Lake's aesthetic and Eastside food scene drives high occupancy in smaller apartments and mid-century homes.</p>
        <p>These neighborhoods have specific appliance patterns. WeHo Airbnbs are often compact apartments with stacked washer-dryer units — the most failure-prone configuration in short-term rental use. Silver Lake's older housing stock runs older appliances that are more likely to need repair. Venice and Santa Monica units face salt air effects on coastal-facing appliances.</p>
        <p>LA's short-term rental regulation landscape under Ordinance 185931 means many hosts are operating single units — their own homes or condos — where a broken appliance has direct personal and financial consequences beyond just the booking.</p>
      </div>
